******************************************************************************
* header_change infile setCT ct <blk>
* header_change infile scale ct scale <blk>
* header_change infile outfile ct
******************************************************************************
  
header_change is a stand-alone program used to modify
certain fields in a FID block header. It may be accessed
directly from a Linux shell tool or via the shell command
within OpenVnmrJ.

There are three forms of this command. In all cases, the first
argument is the path name of the FID file to be used. The second
argument is a keyword 'setCT' or scale or the path name of a file
to which the modified 'infile' will be written.  

If the setCT keyword (case insensitive) is given, the next
argument is the new value of the ctcount field of the FID
block header. An optional block number may also be supplied.
If no block number is given, the ctcount of all the blocks
in the FID file will be modified.

If the scale keyword (case insensitive) is given, the third
argument is the new value of the ctcount field of the FID
block header and the fourth argument is the new value of
the scale field of the FID block header.  An optional final
block number may also be supplied.  If no block number is
given, the ctcount and scale value of all the blocks in the
FID file will be modified. See the scalefid manual for a
description of the functioning of the scale field in the
FID block header.

If the second argument is neither setct nor scale, it is taken
as the file name to which the modified FID file will be written.
The third argument is the value of the new ctcount field in this
modified "outfile".

Examples from a shell tool:
header_change $vnmruser/exp1/acqfil/fid setct 6
header_change $vnmruser/exp1/acqfil/fid scale 2 -1 1
header_change $vnmruser/exp1/acqfil/fid $vnmruser/exp1/acqfil/fid2 5

Examples from within OVJ via the shell command:
write('line3','header_change '+curexp+'/acqfil/fid setct %d',6):$cmd
shell($cmd)
write('line3','header_change '+curexp+'/acqfil/fid scale %d %d %d',2,-1,1):$cmd
shell($cmd)
write('line3','header_change '+curexp+'/acqfil/fid '+curexp+'/acqfil/fid2 %d',5):$cmd
shell($cmd)
